---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { canonicalUrl, SITE_ORIGIN } from "../lib/siteUrls";

const pageDescription =
  "Frequently asked questions about supplement retail environments, pharmacy context, and offline shopping in Singapore.";

const faqUrl = canonicalUrl("/faq");

const breadcrumbJsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  itemListElement: [
    { "@type": "ListItem", position: 1, name: "Home", item: SITE_ORIGIN },
    { "@type": "ListItem", position: 2, name: "FAQ", item: faqUrl },
  ],
});

const webPageJsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  name: "Supplements Shop Singapore | FAQ",
  url: faqUrl,
  description: pageDescription,
  inLanguage: "en-SG",
  isPartOf: {
    "@type": "WebSite",
    name: "Supplement Shop Singapore",
    url: SITE_ORIGIN,
  },
});

const q1 =
  "In everyday search use, “supplements shop singapore” describes intent to learn where supplements are sold and what retail settings exist—pharmacy counters, specialist supplement store sections, or supermarket aisles—not a single endorsed shop. People often compare supplement store singapore options and in-store supplement shopping context before visiting. The phrase maps channel types and availability, not a product recommendation.";

const q2 =
  "Yes. Community and hospital pharmacies in Singapore typically offer health supplements alongside medicines. A licensed pharmacist is usually available, which shapes shelf organisation and how shoppers may ask about label wording or medication interactions. The assortment is generally curated to common vitamin and mineral categories rather than every specialist format.";

const q3 =
  "Many supermarkets and general chains carry a narrow range of familiar supplements near health or personal care. Are supplements sold in supermarkets singapore is a frequent query because shoppers want quick access to mainstream categories. Expect high-turnover lines, not the breadth of a specialist health shop. Shelf placement reflects retailer selection, not clinical advice.";

const q4 =
  "Pharmacy contexts pair product display with dispensary oversight and pharmacist access for factual questions. Specialist health stores often stock wider categories and formats, but staff roles vary and may not include a pharmacist. Pharmacy versus supplement store singapore mainly differs in professional services and range, not in whether one channel is inherently preferable.";

const q5 =
  "Queries like where to buy supplements in Singapore usually precede a visit: shoppers map channels, hours, and whether advice is available. Supplement retail shelf context singapore differs by lighting, signage, and how much label detail can be read on the floor. The intent is planning and context, not rankings or endorsements.";

const q6 =
  "No. This site does not name stores, compare outlets, or promote specific products. It explains neutral patterns in supplement retail environments and offline shopping. For personal decisions, rely on your own label review and qualified clinical guidance. Nothing here is medical advice or a shopping recommendation.";

const faqJsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  mainEntity: [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: 'What does "supplements shop singapore" usually mean?',
      acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: q1 },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "Are supplements commonly sold in pharmacies in Singapore?",
      acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: q2 },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "Are supplements sold in supermarkets in Singapore?",
      acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: q3 },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "What is the difference between pharmacy and health store context?",
      acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: q4 },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "Why do people search where to buy supplements in Singapore?",
      acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: q5 },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "Is this site recommending specific stores or products?",
      acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: q6 },
    },
  ],
});
---
<BaseLayout
  documentTitle="Supplements Shop Singapore | FAQ"
  description={pageDescription}
  path="/faq"
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "FAQ" }]}
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={breadcrumbJsonLd}></script>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={webPageJsonLd}></script>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={faqJsonLd}></script>

  <h1>Supplements Shop Singapore: Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

  <p class="disclaimer">
    General educational information only. Not medical advice. Consult a qualified clinician for personal guidance.
  </p>

  <p class="lead">
    This page answers neutral questions about how supplements appear across retail in Singapore: what people mean by a supplements shop search, whether pharmacies and supermarkets stock products, and how pharmacy versus health-store settings differ. It is written for supplement retail shelf context and in-store supplement shopping context only—where to buy supplements singapore is treated as a channel question, not a recommendation. Supplement store singapore and pharmacy versus supplement store singapore queries usually reflect planning before a visit: which environments carry which categories, how shelves are organised, and how much information is visible without purchase pressure. Are supplements sold in supermarkets singapore is addressed as a matter of typical assortment, not shopping advice. Nothing here endorses outlets, brands, or outcomes.
  </p>

  <section>
    <h2>What does "supplements shop singapore" usually mean?</h2>
    <p>{q1}</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Are supplements commonly sold in pharmacies in Singapore?</h2>
    <p>{q2}</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Are supplements sold in supermarkets in Singapore?</h2>
    <p>{q3}</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What is the difference between pharmacy and health store context?</h2>
    <p>{q4}</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why do people search where to buy supplements in Singapore?</h2>
    <p>{q5}</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Is this site recommending specific stores or products?</h2>
    <p>{q6}</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Key Takeaway</h2>
    <p>
      A supplements shop singapore search usually signals questions about channel mix: pharmacies with pharmacist access, health-focused stores with wider assortment, and supermarkets with limited shelf sets. Understanding supplement retail shelf context singapore and in-store supplement shopping context helps set expectations before you enter a store. This page summarises environment and availability in neutral terms only. It does not recommend places to buy, rate shops, or suggest products.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Context</h2>
    <div class="cross-reference">
      <p>
        For broader background on the supplement landscape in Singapore, see the <a href="https://supplementsingapore.neoi.jp/">Supplements Singapore guide</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <p class="footer-note">
    Educational content only. Not medical or treatment advice.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
